Velocity
Definition
amount of work  (in story points or other units) that is completed per unit of time (e.g., sprint, day, week, month).
Calculated by:
Amount of work completed / given time. Only items meeting the definition of done
Purpose
To know how much work can be done for project completion estimations

Team Velocity
How often calculated.
At the end of every Sprint
Calculated by:
Historical instances used for forecasting
Purpose
allows the Scrum Master to predict the final completion date of the project, and allows the team to make reasonable commitments regarding the number of story points to agree to work on the upcoming sprint



Capacity
Definition
is a measure of the maximum amount of work that a development team expects to produce in a given sprint
Purpose
Helps avoid any burnout and setting parameters the team to work through


